      "bio": "Robert Henry Speed was a Solicitor and Notary Public with a business address at 13 St Peter's-Gate, Nottingham from at least 1876 until his death in 1914. He lived at 27 Cavendish Road East (The Bishop's House) with his wife Emma (seventh daughter of Joseph Morris of Chilwell). They had at least three children: Walter Hamlyn Speed, Edwin Arney Speed, and Cybil Speed. Robert continued practising as a solicitor and public notary into his late eighties.",
