      "last_name": "Speed",
      "born_year": 1864,
      "bio": "Walter Hamlyn Speed attended Rugby School from 1878 to 1881, then matriculated into the University of London in 1881. He became a solicitor in London in 1885, with his professional address at 18 Sackville Street, London in 1910 and 1917, and earlier at 1 Clement's Inn, Strand and 160 Dashwood House, New Bond Street.\n\nIn 1897 a Walter Hamlyn Speed, solicitor of 1 Clement's Inn, was refused discharge from bankruptcy on the grounds that his assets were insufficient and that he had contributed to his bankruptcy by rash and hazardous speculation, unjustifiable extravagance, and culpable neglect of his business affairs. He had died by 1926. He possibly married Charlotte Mary Speed.",
